    "description": "The matchCase flag is inverted in createRegExp. When options.matchCase is true (meaning user wants case-sensitive search), the code adds the 'i' flag which makes the regex case-insensitive. This is backwards. If matchCase is true, we should NOT add the 'i' flag. This breaks case-sensitive search throughout the editor (find/replace, bracket matching, search workers).",
